.md with a threshold configuration table and\n  explicit note that medium-risk findings are treated as warnings\n- Keeps medium: warn as the baseline scan policy for this demo app", "files": [{"path": "policy/zap_policy.yml", "content": "# ZAP baseline scan policy thresholds for the local demo application.\n# Risk levels: high, medium, low\n# Actions: fail (block scan), warn (report as warning), pass (accept)\nthresholds:\n  high: fail\n  medium: warn\n  low: pass\n"}, {"path": "docs/policy.md", "content": "# ZAP Policy\n\nThe local demo policy treats high-risk alerts as failures, medium-risk alerts as warnings, and low-risk alerts as pass-level findings.\n\n## Threshold configuration\n\nDefined in `policy/zap_policy.yml`:\n\n| Risk Level | Action | Description |\n|------------|--------|-------------|\n| High       | fail   | Blocks the baseline scan |\n| Medium     | warn   | Reported as warnings |\n| Low        | pass   | Accepted without flagging |\n\nThese thresholds ensure that the baseline scan treats medium-risk findings as warnings for this demo application.\n"}]}, "id": "call_7b58562e86224e1eb08cfd0b", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7729, "output_tokens": 10725, "total_tokens": 18454, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7552}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 10242}}}}]}}}
