{"ts": "2026-06-08T01:28:05.364336+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Both push methods failed with a **403 (Resource not accessible by personal access token)** error. The token I'm operating with lacks write permissions to this repository, so I cannot commit changes directly.\n\nLet me summarize what I found and the changes I would make:\n\n---\n\n## Issue #3 Analysis & Proposed Changes\n\n### Current State\n\nBoth target files **already implement** the requested behavior:\n\n- **`policy/zap_policy.yml`** — sets `medium: warn` (medium-risk findings are treated as warnings)\n- **`docs/policy.md`** — documents this behavior\n\n### Proposed Enhancements (to better fulfill the issue)\n\n**1. `policy/zap_policy.yml`** — Add documentation comments:\n```yaml\n# ZAP baseline scan policy thresholds for the local demo application.\n# Risk levels: high, medium, low\n# Actions: fail (block scan), warn (report as warning), pass (accept)\nthresholds:\n  high: fail\n  medium: warn\n  low: pass\n```\n\n**2. `docs/policy.md`** — Add a threshold table and explicit medium-risk note:\n```markdown\n# ZAP Policy\n\nThe local demo policy treats high-risk alerts as failures, medium-risk alerts as warnings, and low-risk alerts as pass-level findings.\n\n## Threshold configuration\n\nDefined in `policy/zap_policy.yml`:\n\n| Risk Level | Action | Description |\n|------------|--------|-------------|\n| High       | fail   | Blocks the baseline scan |\n| Medium     | warn   | Reported as warnings |\n| Low        | pass   | Accepted without flagging |\n\nThese thresholds ensure that the baseline scan treats medium-risk findings as warnings for this demo application.\n```\n\n### Validation\nThe validation script (`make validate`) only checks for required file existence and the non-local target rejection guard in `run_zap_baseline.sh`. These documentation changes would not break validation.\n\n### Limitation\nI was unable to commit due to **403 permissions** on the repository. A maintainer with write access would need to apply these changes.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 471, "prompt_tokens": 8548, "total_tokens": 9019, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 46, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8256, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0005665116, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001567416, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00040977}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780882076-5jGfbGG3WRlnCIyLFJFN", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea4d7-f368-7a80-afca-bb68fc50a162-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8548, "output_tokens": 471, "total_tokens": 9019, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8256}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 46}}}}]}}}
